    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nUsing a formatting command like `gqip`, `gwip`, etc., repeatedly within insert-normal mode (i.e. CTRL-O from within insert mode) causes the text to keep toggling between two states. I first described this behavior [here](https://vi.stackexchange.com/questions/40123/insert-mode-gqip-not-idempotent) in a bit more detail, but the info below is self-contained.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\r\n\r\nCopy the following text:\r\n\r\n```\r\nxx xx xxx xx xxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxx xxxxxxxxxxx x xxxxx xxx xxxx xxx x xx\r\nxxxxxx xxx xxxxxxx xxxxxx xx x xxx xx xxx xxxxxx xx xxxxxx xx xxx xxx xx xx\r\nxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxx xxxx xx xx xxxx xxxx xxx xx xx\r\nxxxx xx x xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx xx xx xxxx x xxxxxxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xx\r\nxxx xxx xxx xxx xxxx\r\n```\r\n\r\nPaste in nvim with `\"+P`.\r\n\r\nType `i`.\r\n\r\nType CTRL-O followed by `gqip`. The text changes to:\r\n\r\n```\r\nxx xx xxx xx xxxx xx xxxxx xxxxxxxx xxxxx xxxxxxxxxxx x xxxxx xxx xxxx xxx x xx\r\nxxxxxx xxx xxxxxxx xxxxxx xx x xxx xx xxx xxxxxx xx xxxxxx xx xxx xxx xx xx\r\nxxxxx xxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xxxxxxxxx xx xxx xxxxx xxxx xx xx xxxx xxxx xxx xx xx\r\nxxxx xx x xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx xx xx xxxx x xxxxxxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxx\r\nxx xxx xxx xxx xxx xxxx\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhile still in insert mode, repeatedly typing CTRL-O followed by `gqip` causes the text to toggle between the above two states.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe text should settle on a single state, specifically the first one shown above.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-944+g89722ddfa\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, vim 8.2.1895\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwindows command prompt\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nblank?\n\n### Installation\n\ndownloaded nvim-win64.zip from nightly releases",
